  <language>en_US</language>
  <keyword>rem</keyword>
  <short_description>Remainder after division.</short_description>

  <syntax>
    <syntax_item>C = rem(A, B)</syntax_item>
  </syntax>
  
  <param_input>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>A</param_name>
      <param_description>a variable: dividend</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>B</param_name>
      <param_description>a variable: divisor</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
  </param_input>

  <param_output>

    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>C</param_name>
      <param_description>result of rem(A, B)</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
  </param_output>

  <description>
    <p><b
      >C = rem(A, B)</b> computes the remainder of A and B, i.e : A - fix(A ./ B) .* B.</p>
    <p>This function manages also negative values.</p>
    <p>mod(A, 0) = A , whereas rem(A, 0) = NaN.</p>
    <p>mod(A, B) has the sign of B, while rem(A, B) has the sign of A.</p>
    <p>mod and rem are equals if A and B have the same sign.</p>
  </description>


